<HL>
   Wiser Oil Opens Texas Plant
</HL>
<DATE>
06/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2
</SO>
<CO>
   WISE
</CO>
<LP>
   SISTERSVILLE, W.Va. -- Wiser Oil Co. said it began
operating a natural gas liquids plant in Concho County,
Texas, to process gas from the company's Aqaritta oilfield.
   The plant is removing 7,500 gallons a day of natural gas
liquids from 1.2 million cubic feet a day of natural gas,
Wiser said. The gas is being reinjected into the field to
maintain pressure and enhance oil recovery.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Wiser said that oil production from the field is 700
barrels a day, and that additional drilling will be required
to delineate the limits of the field. Wiser has a 62.5%
working interest and a 50% net revenue interest in the field.
</TEXT>
