<HL>
   REVIEW &amp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:
   Saint Madonna
</HL>
<DATE>
06/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A14
</SO>
<LP>
   Rock reviewers in New York City are doing some nimble
writing about Madonna's "Blond Ambition" concert, in which
she performed in a "dominatrix" outfit, is attended on a red
velvet bed by male dancers and kicks on the ground her two
female backup singers, among other things. One local critic
wrote: "She pushed the limits of morality but never once went
over the edge." Maybe theologians should be reviewing this
show.
</LP>
