<LP>
   SALEM, N.H. -- Hadco Corp. said it bought back from its
chairman Horace H. Irvine II 300,000 shares of common stock;
the company also bought 100,000 shares of common from trusts
he established, all at $4.875 a share, or a total of $1.9
million.
   Following the stock sales, Mr. Irvine and trusts he
created hold 3,884,216 shares of Hadco common, or about 37%
of Hadco's shares outstanding. The company said Mr. Irvine
agreed he won't trade additional shares in the open market
this year.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Hadco, a maker of printed circuit boards, also said its
board authorized the purchase of up to $2 million of
additional shares in the open market this year. And Hadco
directors said they won't sell their stock holdings this
year.
