<HL>
   Dividend News:
   Progressive Bank Inc.
   Omits Its Dividend
</HL>
<DATE>
06/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C9
</SO>
<CO>
   PSBK
</CO>
<IN>
DIVIDENDS (DIV)
</IN>
<LP>
   PAWLING, N.Y. -- Progressive Bank Inc., which cut its
quarterly dividend to 12.5 cents a share from 27.5 cents for
the first quarter, omitted the payout for the second period
and added $5 million to its reserve against possible losses
on bad loans.
   The board omitted the dividend because the real estate
market continues to be weak and nonperforming loans -- those
not earning interest -- have increased, Progressive said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   E. Hale Mayer, chairman and chief executive officer, said,
however, that after the charge, the company's capital stands
at 8.63% of total assets, exceeding regulators' requirements.
   Progressive, holding company for Pawling Savings Bank,
last paid out 12.5 cents a share April 30. It currently has
2.9 million shares outstanding. The total reserve for
possible loan losses is $14.5 million.
   The company's shares were halted in national
over-the-counter trading yesterday before the market opened.
They last traded at $7.75.
</TEXT>
