Treasury's five-year note. Rated single-A-2 by Moody's and
single-A-minus by S&amp;P, the issue will be sold through
underwriters led by Smith Barney, Harris Upham &amp; Co.
                                                                                                       

                      MUNICIPAL
                                                                                                       

   New York City -- $710 million of general obligation bonds
due Feb. 15 and Aug. 1, 1991-2028, tentatively priced by a
Merrill Lynch Capital Markets group to yield from 6.40% in
1991 to 7.90% in 2018-2028. There are no term bonds. The
bonds are rated single-A-minus by S&amp;P. The rating is still
under review by Moody's, but a single-A rating is expected,
according to an official with the lead underwriter.
   Port Authority of New York and New Jersey -- $100 million
of consolidated revenue bonds, 69th Series, due Dec. 1,
1991-1999, and June 1, 2025, with capital appreciation bonds
due Dec. 1, 2000-2011, priced by a Merrill Lynch Capital
Markets group to yield from 5.90% in 1991 to 7.28% in 2025.
Current interest serial bonds are priced at par to yield from
5.90% in 1991 to 6.70% in 1999. The 6.80% serial bonds due in
1999 are priced at par. There is $27.8 million of 7 1/8% term
bonds priced at 98 to yield 7.28% due June 1, 2025. Capital
appreciation bonds are priced to yield from 6.80% in 2000 to
7.10% in 2007-2011. The bonds are rated
single-A-1/double-A-minus.
   Franklin County, Ohio -- $97.5 million of convention
center revenue bonds due Dec. 1, 1994-1999, 2019 and 2020,
with capital appreciation bonds due 2000-2010, tentatively
priced by a PaineWebber Inc. group to yield from 6.30% in
1994 to 7.23% in 2019. Current interest serial bonds are
priced at par to yield from 6.30% in 1994 to 6.80% in 1999.
There are $52 million of 7% term bonds priced at 97 1/4 to
yield 7.23% in 2019 and $8 million of 6% term bonds priced at
86 to yield 7.13% in 2020. Capital appreciation bonds are
priced to yield from 6.90% in 2000 to 7.20% in 2008-2010. The
bonds are insured and triple-A-rated.
   Albuquerque, N.M. -- $88 million of Joint Water and Sewer
System revenue bonds, Series 1990A, due July 1, 2015, with
capital appreciation bonds due 2003-2008 and Series B, due
1991-2003 and 2006, tentatively priced by a Smith Barney
group to yield from 6.15% in 1991 to 7.22% in 2015. Series A
consists of $41.8 million of 6% bonds priced at 86 to yield
7.22% in 2015. Capital appreciation bonds are priced to yield
from 7.10% in 2003 and 2004 to 7.20% in 2007 and 2008. Series
B current interest serial bonds are priced to yield from
6.15% in 1992 to 7.05% in 2003. Serial bonds due in 1991 are
not formally reoffered. There are $13.4 million of 7% term
bonds priced at 98.58 to yield 7.15% in 2006. The bonds are
rated single-A-1/double-A, except for capital appreciation
bonds, which are insured and triple-A-rated.
   Connecticut Housing Finance Authority -- $83.8 million of
housing bonds due Nov. 15, 1995-2004 and 2009, tentatively
priced by a Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc. group to yield from
6.50% in 1995 to 7.50% in 2009. Current interest serial bonds
are priced at par to yield from 6.50% in 1995 to 7.40% in
2004. There are $24.2 million of 7 1/2% term bonds priced at
par due in 2009. Ratings of double-A/double-A-plus are
expected, according to an official with the lead underwriter.
Interest on the bonds will be treated as a preference item in
calculating the federal alternative minimum tax that may be
imposed on certain investors.
   Maryland-National Capital Park Commission -- $59.2 million
of various purpose and refunding revenue bonds due 1991-2010.
A Harris Trust &amp; Savings Bank group placed the winning bid
for $40 million of various purpose and refunding revenue
bonds secured by Prince Georges County, Md. The bonds, rated
double-A/double-A, were priced for reoffering to yield from
5.90% in 1991 to 7.00% in 2008-2010. The remainder of the
issue, $19.2 million of various purpose revenue bonds secured
by Montgomery County, Md., was won by a Merrill Lynch Capital
Markets group. The bonds, rated triple-A, were priced for
reoffering to yield from 6.00% in 1992 to 6.95% in 2008-2010.
Bonds due in 1991 are not formally reoffered.
   Rosemont, Ill. -- $59 million of general obligation
corporate purpose bonds, 1990 Series A, due Dec. 1,
1995-2002, with Series B capital appreciation bonds due
1992-2006 and Series C capital appreciation bonds due
1991-2007, tentatively priced by a Smith Barney group to
yield from 6.20% for bonds due in 1991 to 7.25% in 2006 and
2007. Series A consists of current interest serial bonds
priced at par to yield from 6.40% in 1995 to 7.05% in 2002.
Series B capital appreciation bonds are priced to yield to
maturity from 6.30% in 1992 to 7.25% in 2006. Series C
capital appreciation bonds are priced to yield from 6.20% in
1991 to 7.25% in 2006 and 2007. The bonds are insured and
triple-A-rated.
                                                                                                       

